<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kerrigan</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-24 03:33:09</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>#1 Im not twinked, so dont think it. I used to do alot of barting in East Commons to gain money up to get my armor I have now. now read further to get my analysis of the RLP.<BR>
<BR>
Ive noticed that using a Collar of Undead Protection (has the same 5AC that the Runed Lava Pendant does) compared to a 7agi/7dex Black Pearl Choker. <BR>
<BR>
I gained 36 AC with the 7agi/7dex choker!!! The 5AC didnt mean squat compared to the 7AGI. But I found a way to work around it and gain some stats through the RLP. Read Further to get a GREAT line up for some added stats...<BR>
<BR>
yes, Agility does make a difference in your AC! Im getting one of these Runed Lava Pendents for the 6str (which I need due to Im a Dark elf). <BR>
<BR>
I replaced my 4str 2int earings and I will get back my AGI with 2 Obsidien Bead Hoops 2ac 3agi 3int (very nice for SK's). I then get the Runed Lavapendent giving me and extra 5AC plus I get back my STR I lost! <BR>
<BR>
Ok I didnt get all my agi back.. 1 point.. and I didnt get back all my str. 2 points.. a big woop! but I did gain 5 extra AC!<BR>
<BR>
If I were you SK's I would focus on AC first, Then focus on AGI jacking up your AC/Defense for being the TANKS we should be. Why let warriors have all the fun? Try it out for yourself you'll see the difference in battle. I do alot of Armor switching to check out stats. <BR>
<BR>
If you would like to know what kind of Armor stats Im running on send me a email at insaine_creed@yahoo.com and Ill give you a run down on how to get the best AC out of armor. just a hint. Im hitting 799 AC w/ the shadow Vortex spell (self buff) thats not to far than most untwinked Warriors of the same lvl.<BR>
<BR>
Kerrigan Ner'zhul <BR>
lvl 41 SK <BR>
of Cazic Thule Server</font></td></tr></table>
