<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Yamazaki</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2001-01-09 07:03:58</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok, now people... to clear up some confussion...  I would just like to state one thing... (for a tank) AC IS NOT KING...  Now I would like to state another thing...  It all depends on your situation.  Now with that in mind, lets go over the different possibilites that will now prove my point.  If you are going on a Nagy raid - Fire Resistance should be your best friend, along with magic.  If you are going on a Vox raid - Cold resistance, followed by magic is of course better than AC.  Now, what if you are soloing, and you are dependent on your weapon procs (say darkness or poison or what not), then Dex is now your best friend, considering that since you probably bought a grip of SoW potions, you will never get into melee anyway.  If you are fighting casters that do more damage from spells, I am sure you can sacrifice some ac for resistance spells.  Now, you guys dont think i am one sided, AC rocks when your fighting more things, but it is not always KING, so please keep that in mind.  Of course a Tank's primary job is to soak the blows so that the nukers can either Ice Comet or, AoE the mob you just trainned though karnors... (guys who ever thought up that tactic is a geneous!)  Anyway, I hope this cleared some things up.  (As for this item, I like it because its a good balance)<BR>
Yamazaki Ryuji<BR>
House Ryuji<BR>
of the 40th Blade</font></td></tr></table>
